  "chapter": {
    "number": 21,
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "content": [
          "The King’s Heart"
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 1,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The king’s heart is a waterway in the hand of the LORD;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "He directs it where He pleases.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 2,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All a man’s ways seem right to him,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the LORD weighs the heart.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 3,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "To do righteousness and justice",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is more desirable to the LORD than sacrifice.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 4,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Haughty eyes and a proud heart—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the guides of the wicked—are sin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 5,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The plans of the diligent bring plenty,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "as surely as haste leads to poverty.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 6,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Making a fortune by a lying tongue",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "is a vanishing mist, a deadly pursuit.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 7,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The violence of the wicked will sweep them away",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because they refuse to do what is just.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 8,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The way of a guilty man is crooked,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the conduct of the innocent is upright.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 9,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better to live on a corner of the roof",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than to share a house with a quarrelsome wife.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 10,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The soul of the wicked man craves evil;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "his neighbor finds no favor in his eyes.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 11,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "When a mocker is punished, the simple gain wisdom;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and when a wise man is instructed, he acquires knowledge.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 12,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The Righteous One",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4242
          },
          {
            "text": "considers the house of the wicked",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and brings the wicked to ruin.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 13,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Whoever shuts his ears to the cry of the poor,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "he too shall cry out and receive no answer.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 14,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A gift in secret soothes anger,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and a covert bribe",
            "poem": 2
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4243
          },
          {
            "text": "pacifies great wrath.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 15,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Justice executed is a joy to the righteous,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a terror to the workers of iniquity.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 16,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The man who strays from the path of understanding",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "will rest in the assembly of the dead.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 17,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who loves pleasure will become poor;",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "the one who loves wine and oil will never be rich.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 18,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The wicked become a ransom for the righteous,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and the faithless for the upright.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 19,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Better to live in the desert",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "than with a contentious and ill-tempered wife.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 20,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Precious treasures and oil are in the dwelling of the wise,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but a foolish man consumes them.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 21,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who pursues righteousness and loving devotion",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "finds life, righteousness, and honor.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 22,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A wise man scales the city of the mighty",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "and pulls down the stronghold in which they trust.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 23,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "He who guards his mouth and tongue",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "keeps his soul from distress.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 24,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mocker is the name of the proud and arrogant man—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "of him who acts with excessive pride.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 25,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The craving of the slacker kills him",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "because his hands refuse to work.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 26,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "All day long he covets more,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the righteous give without restraint.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 27,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "The sacrifice of the wicked is detestable—",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "how much more so when brought with ill intent!",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 28,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A lying witness will perish,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but the man who listens to truth will speak forever.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 29,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A wicked man hardens his face,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "noteId": 4244
          },
          {
            "text": "but the upright man makes his way sure.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 30,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "There is no wisdom, no understanding, no counsel",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "that can prevail against the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "line_break"
      },
      {
        "type": "verse",
        "number": 31,
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "A horse is prepared for the day of battle,",
            "poem": 1
          },
          {
            "text": "but victory is of the LORD.",
            "poem": 2
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
    "footnotes": [
